The Maintenance Window meeting is scheduled for:
  UTC: 2024-03-31T01:30:00
  (This is during the DST transition on March 31, 2024)

OLD BUGGY METHOD:
  Result: 2024-03-31 01:30:00 CET+0100
  ❌ WRONG! Shows 02:30 CET, but 2am-3am doesn't exist on DST day!

NEW CORRECT METHOD:
  Result: 2024-03-31 03:30:00 CEST+0200
  ✓ CORRECT! Shows 03:30 CEST (clocks jumped from 2am to 3am)

EXPLANATION:
  On March 31, 2024, Europe/Berlin switched to DST at 2:00am.
  Clocks jumped forward: 01:59:59 CET → 03:00:00 CEST
  The hour from 2:00-2:59 doesn't exist!
  
  The bug: localize() on a naive datetime assumes it's already
           in that timezone, so 01:30 UTC became 01:30 CET.
  
  The fix: First mark as UTC, then convert to Berlin timezone,
           which properly adds the DST offset (+2 hours).

======================================================================
