[?2004huser@e09899677ebe:~/scheduler$ cat > FIX_SUMMARY.md << 'EOF'
[?2004l[?2004h> # Scheduler DST Bug Fix Summary
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Problem
[?2004l[?2004h> Meeting reminders were being sent at incorrect times - off by exactly one hour, but **only for meetings between 2am-3am local time** (Europe/Berlin). This specifically affected the Monday 2:30am maintenance window reminder.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Root Cause
[?2004l[?2004h> The bug was in the `convert_to_berlin()` function in `/home/user/scheduler/app.py`.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ### The Buggy Code:
[?2004l[?2004h> ```python
[?2004l[?2004h> def convert_to_berlin(utc_time_str):
[?2004l[?2004h>     utc_dt = datetime.strptime(utc_time_str, '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S')
[?2004l[?2004h>     # BUG: This treats the UTC time as if it's already Berlin time
[?2004l[?2004h>     berlin_dt = BERLIN_TZ.localize(utc_dt)
[?2004l[?2004h>     return berlin_dt
[?2004l[?2004h> ```
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> **What was wrong:**
[?2004l[?2004h> - `BERLIN_TZ.localize()` was called on a naive datetime parsed from a UTC string
[?2004l[?2004h> - This incorrectly treated the UTC timestamp as if it were already in Berlin timezone
[?2004l[?2004h> - During DST transitions (when clocks jump from 2am to 3am), this caused a 1-hour offset
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ### The Fix:
[?2004l[?2004h> ```python
[?2004l[?2004h> def convert_to_berlin(utc_time_str):
